<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/353f32bb2a2351e48639883cf11bdd55.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 7 and A = 35 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>10.0</li><li>12.2</li><li>55.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({35}\right)}}}=\frac{{7}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{7}}{{\tan{{\left({35}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{9.9970360471948}\approx{10}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={7}^{{2}}+{9.9970360471948}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={49}+{99.940729728912}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={148.94072972891}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{148.94072972891}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{12.204127569348}\approx{12.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{35}^{\circ}\approx{55}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

